articles.author: Matthew Elder
articles.description: Ange Postecoglou insists Celtic do not have any pyschological edge over Rangers ahead of Sunday's Old Firm derby despite producing one of their best displays of the season in the 4-0 mauling of Hibs at Easter Road.
articles.title: 'I don't like that word' - Ange Postecoglou dismisses Celtic momentum talk ahead of Rangers clash

articles.author: Alan Pattullo
articles.description: Lee Johnson has stressed that as far as he is aware Ryan Porteous was not saying his farewells to the Easter Road crowd after Hibs' 4-0 defeat to Celtic.
articles.title: Lee Johnson: Porteous not saying his farewells "to my knowledge"; Hibs can compete v Hearts

articles.author: Alan Pattullo
articles.description: Sometimes it seems as if Celtic might never lose again. They rounded off 2022 in style with a dominant win after withstanding a strong opening from Hibs.
articles.title: Celtic send Rangers warning with dominant Hibs showing as Aaron Mooy opens account

articles.author: Angus Wright
articles.description: Chelsea are reportedly considering a move for Celtic right-back Josip Juranovic after Reece James suffered another injury in their win over Bournemouth on Tuesday night.
articles.title: Celtic star 'on Chelsea radar' for January move after injury to key player

articles.author: Moira Gordon
articles.description: Hibs, quite literally, weren’t in the same league as Celtic when the Parkhead side completed their Invincibles season, and although they share the same division these days, Paul Hanlon says there are still times when the defending champions appear on a different level from the rest.
articles.title: Paul Hanlon wary of 'relentless' Celtic but insists Hibs cannot 'sit back and wait to be beaten'

articles.author: Andrew Smith
articles.description: There is no chance of Rangers looking beyond their hosting of Motherwell and towards their derby clash at Ibrox that follows it, according to Michael Beale.
articles.title: Michael Beale explains why Rangers should only be three points behind Celtic

articles.author: Andrew Smith
articles.description: It isn’t always the case that a player will be pleased at being presented with the sternest challenge possible.
articles.title: Celtic's Carl Starfelt addresses Kevin Nisbet tackle accusations  - 'I cannot see how you can say that'

articles.author: Angus Wright
articles.description: Celtic are reportedly preparing to terminate their loan deal with Rubin Kazan for midfielder Oliver Abildgaard.
articles.title: Celtic 'set to terminate loan deal' in rare Ange Postecoglou signing failure

articles.author: Angus Wright
articles.description: Former Celtic defender Jeremie Frimpong is a reported transfer target for Real Madrid.
articles.title: Celtic eye major sell-on fee as Real Madrid 'make enquiry' for €50m-rated former Hoops star

articles.author: Mark Atkinson
articles.description: Celtic manager Ange Postecoglou does not believe complacency will set into his team despite a nine-point lead at the top of the cinch Premiership and an unbeaten domestic run throughout this season.
articles.title: 'I've always sensed it': Celtic boss Ange Postecoglou assesses squad's mindset ahead of facing Hibs and Rangers

articles.author: Moira Gordon
articles.description: Buoyed by the win over Livingston on Christmas Eve, Hibs manager Lee Johnson says his men will have to shift up through the gears when they tackle Celtic on Wednesday.
articles.title: Hibs boss makes unusual Celtic remark as discusses Puntos and Formula One races

articles.author: Mark Atkinson
articles.description: Scotland starlet Ben Doak has made his English Premier League debut after coming on as a late substitute for Liverpool in their 3-1 win over Aston Villa.

articles.author: Andrew Smith
articles.description: St Johnstone midfielder Cammy MacPherson has suggested that VAR interventions provide a welcome relief when facing up to a relentless Celtic and their multi-ball approach in the east end of Glasgow.
articles.title: Why VAR interventions are helping teams when they play Celtic

articles.author: Andrew Smith
articles.description: Celtic’s evergreen winger James Forrest derives warranted satisfaction from having become the club’s third man.
articles.title: 'I just hope I can keep doing that as long as I’m here': The Celtic star who has joined an elite club

articles.author: Mark Atkinson
articles.description: Celtic are on the brink of signing Japan internationalist Tomoki Iwata from Yokohama F Marinos, according to reports in his homeland.

articles.author: Mark Atkinson
articles.description: Under Ange Postecoglou, there is never a dull transfer window at Celtic. Two players have already been snapped up for the start of next year – but that is likely to just be the start of a busy month at Parkhead.
